column1: NET - 008 - Closeout review comments on Keys Mgmt Plan
column32: Incorporate feedback and closeout feedback on Keys Mgmt Plan

The delay in ordering the OpenGear equipment jeopardizes production readiness for the East Colo after the May 1 operational readiness.

Kyndryl is to procure the Lighthouse equipment for OOB service, and the hardware BOM is complete.

It is requested the Kyndryl Amd to procure both P2P and the OpenGear equipment be tied to the the same discussion.

OOB equipment has a 12-14 week lead time and the delay in procuring the equipment jeopardizes the East Colo operational readiness.  See comments below.
column153:
18/Feb/22 8:59 AM;Ben.Taylor@rtx.com;The presentation of the Kyndryl pricing is bundled with the presentation of the Rubrik pricing at the request of Steve Vesta.

The date for presenting the OOB pricing is pushing to 2/18 and possibly 2/21.;;;

column1: NET - 015 - hRTN TEM - Communicate Transition Plan

column32: Communications with DXC regarding contract separation/termination

Until Cisco receives the PO from Kyndryl, Cisco will not reserve the certified refurbished switches.

If the switches are not ordered, the camera system will not be available, and the DC operational readiness date of May 1 is in jeopardy.

The DC leadership team has authorized the use of Certified Cisco refurbished switches from Cisco.  These switches are available now and have less the four (4) week lead time.

Kyndryl will not issue a PO until the Amd to their contract authorizes the purchase.

column1: NET-013 - Third Party Remote Access Solution – Pulse BPAR – SAP Created

column32:
The development of the CRD documents for the data center build out has shifted to the WWT Technical Design Team from Kyndryl.

WWT will have limited resources after 2/28/2022 to create the build documents.

The CRD documents are required by RTX to build out the components within the data center and need to be available when the hardware arrives.

14 CRD documents need to be developed, one CRD for each data center, the East Colo and PDC1:
 # VX Rail
 # Dell ECS
 # Dell PowerScale
 # Dell MX7000
 # Dell PowerStore
 # Cisco Switches
 # OpenGear OOB

column1: T2T - A user's UPN should be converted to include the E or C to employee ID(ADX ID) prior to mailbox migration (ADX end state UPN configuration) to avoid requiring the user to reconfigure their Outlook profile after migration
column32:
A user's UPN should be converted to include the E or C prior to mailbox migration (ADX end state UPN configuration).

D-041

*Impact:*

If the UPN is converted after a user's mailbox has migrated, the user will have to reconfigure their Outlook profile. 

*Project Manager*

Courtney Schultz

*Owner*

Kyle Brower/Deb Carter
column153:
11/Feb/22 1:22 PM;Stephanie.Turlington@rtx.com;*Owner:* Kyle Brower/Deb Carter
